Formula: $$ \Delta v_c=v_C(0)+\frac{1}{C}\int_0^t i_C(\tau)\,d\tau$$ We get told that $v_c(0us)=0$

Therefore: $$\Delta v_C=\frac{1}{C}\int_0^{10\mu s} i_C(t)\,dt =\frac{1}{C}\Big[(2.5+i_A)(3\mu s)+i_A(7\mu s)\Big].$$

Then: $$(2.5+i_A)(3\mu s)+i_A(7\mu s) = 0$$ Isolate $i_A$:

In[3]:
from sympy import *
x = symbols("x")
solve(Eq((2.5+x)*(3)+x*7, 0))
Out[3]:
[-0.750000000000000]

Therefore: $\boxed{i_A=-0.75A}$

Since: $i_c=i_s-i_A$ $$v_C(3\mu s)=\frac{1}{C}\int_0^{3\mu s} i_C(t)\,dt =\frac{1}{220\mu F} \cdot (2.5A-0.75A)\, \cdot 3\mu s =\frac{5.25\mu C}{220\mu F}\approx 0.0239V = 23.9mV$$

Therefore: $v_C(3\mu s) \approx 23.9mV$
